						<summary>

						<p>A (second) sculptured stone near the tank bund.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to about the 10th century A.D., on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to record the death of a warrior (name lost) at the hands of Vasantōju. It also gives the epithets of the victim <hi rend="italic">Sāvanta Ganṟu, Ugrampali</hi> etc.</p>						

						</summary>
